Package com.intellij.util.containers

Class UnmodifiableHashMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.util.containers.UnmodifiableHashMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - type of the map keys
    V - type of the map values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>

    public final class UnmodifiableHashMap<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map<K,V>
    An immutable unordered hash-based map which optimizes incremental growth and may have custom equals/hashCode strategy. This map doesn't support null keys, but supports null values. This map is not serializable.

      • with

        public UnmodifiableHashMap<K,V> with(K key,
                                     V value)
        Returns an UnmodifiableHashMap which contains all the entries as this map plus the supplied mapping
        Parameters:
        key - a key to add/replace
        value - a value to associate with the key
        Returns:
        an UnmodifiableHashMap which contains all the entries as this map plus the supplied mapping. May return the same map if given key is already associated with the same value. Note however that if value is not the same but equal object, the new map will be created as sometimes it's desired to replace the object with another one which is equal to the old object.

      • withAll

        public UnmodifiableHashMap<K,V> withAll(java.util.Map<? extends K,? extends V> map)
        Returns an UnmodifiableHashMap which contains all the entries as this map plus all the mappings of the supplied map.
        Parameters:
        map - to add entries from
        Returns:
        an UnmodifiableHashMap which contains all the entries as this map plus all the mappings of the supplied map. May (but not guaranteed) return the same map if the supplied map is empty or all its mappings already exist in this map (assuming values are compared by reference). The equals/hashCode strategy of the resulting map is the same as the strategy of this map.
